channel.description:
Hi, You are adding a feature that will allow you to do owner commands without having a crown (Hidden Owner).

Step 1 : Open commands.java 

Step 2 : Search for something similar to this :
[code]
    if (c.playerRights >= 0)
        playerCommands(c, playerCommand);
    if (c.playerRights == 1 || c.playerRights == 2 || c.playerRights == 3)
        moderatorCommands(c, playerCommand);
    if (c.playerRights == 2 || c.playerRights == 3)
        administratorCommands(c, playerCommand);
    if (c.playerRights == 3)
        ownerCommands(c, playerCommand);
    if (c.playerRights >= 1)
        DonatorCommands(c, playerCommand);[/code]

Step 3 : At the end of all the lines add " || c.isHiddenOwner())". For example 

[code]    if (c.playerRights == 3)
        ownerCommands(c, playerCommand);[/code]

Would turn into

[code]    if (c.playerRights == 3 || c.isHiddenOwner())
        ownerCommands(c, playerCommand);[/code]

Step 4 : Save and Open Player.java

Step 5 : Search for "public abstract class Player {"

Step 6 : Under it add 

[code]
    public boolean isHiddenOwner(){
        return playerName.equalsIgnoreCase("YOUR_HIDDEN_OWNER_ACCOUNT_NAME");
    }[/code]

Step 7 : Replace "YOUR_HIDDEN_OWNER_ACCOUNT_NAME" With the name of the account you want to be hidden owner.

Step 8 : Save player.java. Compile and your done.

Now the player name you used will have all commands that you have.
